verbs.description: outbake (third-person singular simple present outbakes, present participle outbaking, simple past and past participle outbaked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To surpass in baking; to bake better than.
examples: The two old ladies were always trying to outbake each other.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To heat (equipment) at low pressure to remove adsorbed gas from surfaces.
